# Vibemetric Development Rules for Cline

## Project Context
AI code detection platform with 4-layer detection system. 152 tests, 85% coverage. Python 3.9+.

## Quick Reference

### Before Coding
- Run `pytest` to verify tests pass
- Check `CONTRIBUTING.md` for guidelines
- Create feature branch

### When Coding
- Add type hints to all functions
- Write tests FIRST (TDD)
- Use Google-style docstrings
- Follow existing patterns in codebase

### Before Committing
```bash
pytest                          # All tests must pass
black src/ tests/               # Format code
ruff check src/ tests/          # Lint code
pytest --cov=vibemetric         # Check coverage
```

### Commit Format
```
type(scope): description

feat(detector): Add new AI tool support
fix(velocity): Handle edge case
test(pattern): Add docstring tests
docs(readme): Update installation
```

## Key Files

- `src/vibemetric/detectors/` - 4 detection layers
- `src/vibemetric/scorer.py` - Score combination
- `src/vibemetric/cli.py` - CLI commands
- `tests/` - Unit tests (152 tests)
- `CONTRIBUTING.md` - Full guidelines

## Testing Pattern

```python
# tests/test_feature.py
import pytest
from vibemetric.module import Class

class TestFeature:
    def test_success_case(self):
        obj = Class()
        result = obj.method()
        assert result == expected
    
    def test_error_case(self):
        obj = Class()
        with pytest.raises(ValueError):
            obj.method(invalid_input)
```

## Don't
- Push to main directly
- Skip tests
- Ignore type hints
- Leave debug code

## Do
- Use feature branches
- Write tests first
- Add docstrings
- Run full test suite
